[EVENT]
xy=[15, 22]
graphic="NPC 01"
direction=E

[PAGE]
trigger=onEventTouch


s:Kernel.pbNoticePlayer( get_character(0))"
Show Text "\\bI stopped you as you walked past."
Show Text "\\bHaving \"Trainer(3)\" as my event's name, and the \Event Touch\ trigger, tells me to activate whenever you enter any of the three tiles in front of me."
Show Text "\\bKernel.pbExclaim makes me exclaim. Kernel.pbNoticePlayer does the same thing, as well as make me approach you."
Show Text "\\bTrainers use these features by default, but other NPCs like me can use them too. Roadblock events in particular love to use them."
Show Text "\\bShall I turn you back like a real roadblock, or should I deactivate myself?"
Show Choices choices=['Roadblock', 'Deactivate'], default=0
When 'Roadblock'
  Show Text "\\bCome back when Game Switch 5 is ON."
  Set Move Route :player
    Turn S
    Step 1F
  Set Move Route :self
    Turn W
    Step W
    Step W
    Step W
    Turn E
  
When 'Deactivate'
  Show Text "\\bOkay. I'll fulfil my roadblock condition myself, by turning the Game Switch I depend on (5) to ON."
  Set Move Route :self
    Turn W
    Step W
    Step W
    Step W
    Turn E
  
  :DefeatedGym2 = :ON
[end]


[PAGE]

:DefeatedGym2 == :ON

Show Text "\\bRoadblock events don't normally set the conditions they wait for (Game Switch 5 in my case), but I did."
[end]

